<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-04T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-04T13:00:00-05:00" n="1272" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1272">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/71.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-04T13:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1912—1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Governor Colquitt of Texas, in a telegram received October 1, 1.15 p.m.,
                            replies to Department’s September 30, as follows:</p>
                        <p>[Telegram quoted.]</p>
                        <p>You may bring the Governor’s suggested amendment of the Mexican
                            Government’s request to the attention of the Minister for Foreign <pb facs="1016" n="900" xml:id="pg_900"/> Affairs, unless you think it
                            necessary for the Mexican Government to make the next move, in view of
                            representations you have already made.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>